{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GdgA9xkTJqEtyK31u1DxUn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"package\", \"spring-boot:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014Ak8MKE3tPoyvfnNFac3bR","session_id":"1d77b2ee-6e15-42d9-9f65-0c272b9a6995","uuid":"9547d073-a53e-45ee-a453-6d6503384b13"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014Ak8MKE3tPoyvfnNFac3bR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, I'll summarize my findings comprehensively:\n\nCOMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE ANALYSIS\n===============================\n\n1. PROJECT OVERVIEW\n-------------------\n- Project Name: Address Book (Spring + JSF)\n- Artifact ID: address-book-spring\n- Version: 0.0.1-SNAPSHOT\n- Packaging: WAR (Web Application Archive)\n\n2. BUILD SYSTEM\n---------------\n- Build Tool: Maven (Maven Wrapper included)\n- Java Version: 17\n- Spring Boot Version: Latest version (not explicitly specified, but recent)\n- Main Build Plugin: spring-boot-maven-plugin\n\n3. SPRING FRAMEWORK DETAILS\n--------------------------\n- Spring Core Version: 6.2.11\n- Spring Boot Starters Used:\n  * spring-boot-starter-data-jpa\n  * spring-boot-starter-web\n  * spring-boot-starter-validation\n  * spring-boot-starter-test\n- Additional Frameworks:\n  * JoinFaces (JSF Integration)\n  * Jakarta Faces 4.0.2\n  * Weld Servlet Core 5.1.0.Final\n\n4. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n---------------------\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__address-book__spring__jakarta/run_3/output/\n├── .mvn/wrapper/\n├── src/\n│   └── main/\n│       ├── java/com/example/addressbookspring/\n│       │   ├── config/\n│       │   ├── entity/\n│       │   ├── repo/\n│       │   ├── service/\n│       │   └── web/\n│       └── resources/\n│           ├── META-INF/\n│           └── (configuration files)\n\n5. JAVA SOURCE FILES & PACKAGES\n-------------------------------\nPackage: com.example.addressbookspring\n- Application.java (Main Spring Boot Application)\n- ServletInitializer.java\n- config/\n  * JsfConfig.java\n  * SpringConfig.java\n- entity/\n  * Contact.java (JPA Entity)\n- repo/\n  * ContactRepository.java (Spring Data JPA Repository)\n- service/\n  * ContactService.java (Business Logic)\n- web/\n  * ContactController.java (REST/Web Controller)\n\n6. CONFIGURATION FILES\n---------------------\n- application.properties\n  * Configures H2 in-memory database\n  * Sets up JSF configurations\n  * Defines server port (8080)\n- META-INF/faces-config.xml (JSF Configuration)\n- ValidationMessages.properties\n- Bundle.properties\n\n7. DATABASE\n-----------\n- Database: H2 In-Memory Database\n- Configuration: \n  * URL: jdbc:h2:mem:addressbook\n  * Username: sa\n  * Password: (empty)\n- Hibernate DDL Auto: update\n- SQL Logging: Enabled\n\n8. WEB RESOURCES\n----------------\n- XHTML Pages:\n  * /contact/Create.xhtml\n  * /contact/Edit.xhtml\n  * /contact/List.xhtml\n  * /contact/View.xhtml\n  * index.xhtml\n  * template.xhtml\n- CSS: jsfcrud.css\n\n9. DOCKERFILE\n-------------\n- Base Image: maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n- Installs additional tools (uv, Python, Playwright)\n- Copies project and runs Maven package and spring-boot:run\n\n10. TEST FILES\n--------------\n- Includes spring-boot-starter-test dependency\n- Specific test files not visible in this snapshot\n\nADDITIONAL OBSERVATIONS\n----------------------\n- Project uses Jakarta EE standards\n- Integrates JSF with Spring Boot\n- Designed as a web-based address book application\n- Uses modern Java and Spring ecosystem practices\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of this project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d77b2ee-6e15-42d9-9f65-0c272b9a6995","uuid":"bde40f96-6f91-4c33-b0db-e0ea789eddbc"}
